<FONT CLASS="ArticleSource"><BIG>Whineplay:</BIG></FONT> 
<FONT CLASS="ArticleHead"><BIG>Listen!  Smell that?</BIG></FONT>
<FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </FONT><FONT CLASS="ArticleAuthor">Kohath</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleTime>09/20/2001 05:49 PM CDT</FONT>
<DIV ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT CLASS=ArticleText>
<b>Thine RP Server Cometh, d00d</b><p>Verant listened to their customers, and created a Roleplay server.  Brad says it's coming soon.<p><b>Just an update on this, since it's been a while:<br>We'll be launching it in 'open beta' mode very soon, similar to how S. Zek initially was launched.<p>As we get closer, we'll post the ruleset as it will be at beta launch.<p>-Brad</b><p>This will be good news for all of you elf-wannabes out there who like to cause people trouble for not roleplaying.  That is, until you actually start a character there.  After you try it out, you'll be disappointed and go back to the other servers.<p>This will be <i>really</i> good news for the people you're pestering.  Now they can tell you where to go without being impolite.<p><b>Click Off</b><p>Verant listens to a complaint here, and Absor says it'll be fixed. <p><b>Mzion-RZ wrote:</b><br><i>Yea, You said all benficatl spells are clickable off, Now Ranger spell lv 39 Call of Sky isnt clickable off i dont think it has a drain component Only reason i am saying this is becuase When i Am grouped with a Chanter ANd want Boon, he cant when CoS up and its really anoying to miss out on boon cuz my dang spell wont click off and i dont feel like Killing all my buffs to kill it isnt worth it either so i would ask for this to be fixed or at least an explaination why</i><p><b>You are correct. We'll get this one fixed with the next patch. Thanks for the heads up.<p>Alan</b><p>Alan, invis doesn't click off either.  Alan?  Are you listening?<p><b>Don't Flock with the British</b><p>But then there's <a href="http://lumthemad.net/story.php?story=2314">this</a>.  The CEO doesn't seem to be a listener.<p>The Tick quotes a <a href="http://www.edge-online.co.uk/default1.asp">British game magazine</a> quoting Kelly Flock (CEO SOE) out of context saying &quot;No, we never talk to consumers - they just fuck us up.&quot;<p>And now I've quoted it even further out of context.  Go read the <a href="http://lumthemad.net/story.php?story=2314">article</a> on the soon-to-be-renamed Lum the Mad to get a slightly less distorted picture of what Mr. Flock was trying to say.<p>Personally, I think he's right if he's talking about game <b>design</b>.  A group of casual (or even power) players is good at complaining about the problems of the game, but lacks the perspective to come up with solutions.  And designs need to have a Vision that can't be provided by focus groups and surveys.  Without a Vision, the end result will lack the edgy appeal that comes from the personal touch of the designers.<p>If Mr. Flock is talking about <b>bugs or problems</b> he's absolutely wrong.  People know when they're having problems.  Ignoring them solves nothing.
</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
